Response ID: resp_279
Response Text: I'd like to see these programs reinstate some of the standard checks and balances that are implemented in like cities across the country. Austin is a young city that has been growing fast. It does not have the luxury of time to allow things to develop. With this city's extreme growth over the past 50 years, it needs to leverage the best practices of what has been done elsewhere rather than create these short-sighted, extremely flawed programs that hurt more than help the existing community. Austin does not need to Ruben the wheel here! Reinstate the requirement of fiscal sponsorship for those that are not 501(c)3 orgs. Deny funding for for-profit orgs. They should never be allowed to compete in the same pool as nonprofits. It is only siphoning tax dollars or of the community into the hands of orgs that are designed to make profits. There should be legitimate training for adjudication of grant applications. There are individuals passing judgements on grant applications with NO working knowledge of the industry!

